San Jose Sharks (1-0-0, fourth in the Pacific) vs. Montreal Canadiens (0-3-0, eighth in the Atlantic)
Montreal; Tuesday, 7 p.m. EDT
FANDUEL SPORTSBOOK
 LINE: Canadiens -132, Sharks +110; over/under is 5.5
BOTTOM LINE: Montreal aims to end its three-game skid when the Canadiens take on San Jose.
Montreal went 24-21-11 overall with a 13-11-4 record at home in the 2020-21 season. The Canadiens were called for 200 penalties last season averaging 3.6 penalties and 8.3 penalty minutes per game.
San Jose went 21-28-7 overall and 10-15-3 on the road a season ago. Goalies for the Sharks allowed 3.3 goals on 31.8 shots per game last season.
The teams face off Tuesday for the first time this season.
INJURIES: Canadiens: None listed.
Sharks: None listed.
